_content\";s:290:\"<h4 style=\"text-align: center\"></h4>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center\"></h4>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">On this page, we\'ll post materials from the presentation,</span> contact information, and other upcoming events for Transitioning attendees.</h4>\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:26:\"Connect with Transitioning\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:26:\"connect-with-transitioning\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2012-10-12 15:08:57\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2012-10-12 15:08:57\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:0;s:4:\"guid\";s:45:\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/?page_id=610\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:9;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:53;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"8\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 18:54:25\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 18:54:25\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:495:\"The Transitioning to College Writing Symposium is only made possible by the collaboration of teachers across the state. Click each group to learn more about how they contributed to this year\'s Symposium.\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/contributors/speakers/\">Featured Speakers</a></h2>\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/contributors/participants/\">Participants</a></h2>\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/contributors/planners/\">Program Planners</a></h2>\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:12:\"Contributors\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:12:\"contributors\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-09-02 19:28:03\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-09-02 19:28:03\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:0;s:4:\"guid\";s:44:\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/?page_id=53\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:10;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:978;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2013-09-20 14:46:40\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2013-09-20 14:46:40\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:1580:\"[responsive_vid]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nWe hope you will participate in this documentary project! We are excited to hear what you have to say about teaching writing in Mississippi and the Memphis area.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Please read and sign the release form before recording your responses.</li>\r\n	<li>Please identify yourself first, including your name and the name of the institution where you teach.</li>\r\n	<li>You may choose which questions to answer in your video response – do not feel obligated to answer them all, but focus on a few which you find particularly compelling, thought-provoking, or worth discussing.</li>\r\n	<li>We particularly would like variety in respondents - we’d love to have good representation from high schools, community colleges and four-year universities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<strong>Questions</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Why do you teach writing?\r\n2. What do you think is the most challenging thing about teaching writing at your institution?\r\n3. What challenges/opportunities does the context of our teaching – in Mississippi and the Memphis area – present?\r\n4. What do you wish students knew before they set foot in your class for the first time?\r\n5. What advice would you give a new teacher who is about to begin their first semester of teaching writing at your institution?\r\n6. What do you wish teachers at other institutions (i.e., community colleges and four-year universities, if you are a high school teacher; high schools and four-year universities, if you are a community college teacher, etc.) knew about how you teach your students?\r\n\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:19:\"Documentary Project\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:11:\"documentary\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2014-09-16 15:44:06\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2014-09-16 15:44:06\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:1126;s:4:\"guid\";s:45:\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/?page_id=978\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:11;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:1120;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2014-09-15 17:09:34\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2014-09-15 17:09:34\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:1130:\"The Mississippi Teachers Talk documentary project continues this year! We will have a place set up on both Friday and Saturday for teachers to talk about their teaching and their students. Teachers may engage with one or more of the following questions:\r\n\r\n<strong>Questions</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Specific Assignments/Strategies:</strong> What is the very best writing assignment you ever gave your students, and what made it so effective?</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Student Engagement in the Writing Process:</strong> How do you foster student engagement in the writing process, from planning to drafting to peer review and revision? What specific strategies do you use?</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Transitioning:</strong> How do you anticipate the expectations of each student’s next academic level when making decisions about your curriculum?</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Evolution of teaching:</strong> How has your approach to teaching writing evolved since your first experience?</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Writing’s Role:</strong> (How) are we, writing teachers, making a difference in our students’ lives?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<hr/>\r\n\r\n[responsive_vid]\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:19:\"Documentary Project\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:11:\"documentary\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2014-09-16 15:49:28\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2014-09-16 15:49:28\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:0;s:4:\"guid\";s:46:\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/?page_id=1120\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:12;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:21;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"8\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 18:25:50\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 18:25:50\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:452:\"The Transitioning symposium will be held on Friday, October 10 and Saturday, October 11, 2014 (there is no home Ole Miss football game scheduled this weekend). The symposium will begin Friday morning and end with a working luncheon on Saturday. Our program has been developed by a committee of teachers of writing from area high schools, community colleges, and the University of Mississippi.\r\n\r\nA copy of the Symposium schedule will be available soon.\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:6:\"Events\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:6:\"events\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modi