\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:16;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:85;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"8\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 19:56:07\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 19:56:07\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:1111:\"<h3 align=\"center\">About our Travel Grants</h3>\r\nThrough generous contributions from Bedford/St. Martin\'s and UM\'s School of Education, we are pleased to offer symposium attendees the opportunity to apply for a symposium grant.\r\n\r\nWhile anyone registered for the symposium may apply for a grant, we prioritize recipients by a combination of factors that include but are not limited to distance traveled, teacher access to professional development funds, school district policy regarding substitute pay, whether the applicant is a new or returning symposium attendee, and the date of application. Up to 20 symposium grants may be awarded.\r\n\r\nThe deadline to apply for a 2015 grant is Friday, October 9, 2015. Recipients of travel grants will receive a check from us via postal service between November 1 and December 15, 2015.\r\n\r\nQuestions regarding travel grants should be sent to <a title=\"email link\" href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\" target=\"_blank\">transitioning@olemiss.edu</a>; phone call inquiries should be directed to 662-915-2121.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"107\" title=\"Grant Application\"]\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:6:\"Grants\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:6:\"grants\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-09-08 15:58:18\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-09-08 15:58:18\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:0;s:4:\"guid\";s:44:\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/?page_id=85\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:17;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:952;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"2\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 13:35:40\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 13:35:40\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:873:\"<h2>Welcome to the Transitioning to College Writing Symposium website, hosted by the Department of Writing and Rhetoric at the University of Mississippi.</h2>\r\nTransitioning to College Writing is an annual symposium for writing teachers from college and high school settings in Mississippi and the Memphis areas. Held on the Ole Miss campus, attendees explore challenges we all face in giving our students the best possible foundation for transitioning to college writing.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_617\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"480\"]<a href=\"http://130.74.44.156/transitioning/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/bobalice.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-617 \" src=\"http://130.74.44.156/transitioning/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/bobalice.jpg\" alt=\"Dr. Bob Cummings addresses TCW 2012 attendees. \" width=\"480\" height=\"360\" /></a> Dr. Bob Cummings addresses TCW 2012 attendees.[/caption]\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:4:\"Home\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:13:\"sample-page-2\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-06-12 21:02:23\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-06-12 21:02:23\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:0;s:4:\"guid\";s:49:\"http://transitioning.blog1.olemiss.edu/?page_id=2\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:18;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:1056;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"1\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2014-08-04 16:32:17\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2014-08-04 16:32:17\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:8:\"CONTENTS\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:9:\"Locations\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:4:\"open\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:9:\"locations\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2014-08-04 16:32:17\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2014-08-04 16:32:17\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:1055;s:4:\"guid\";s:52:\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/events-2/locations/\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s:4:\"page\";s:14:\"post_mime_type\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"comment_count\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"filter\";s:3:\"raw\";}i:19;O:7:\"WP_Post\":24:{s:2:\"ID\";i:16;s:11:\"post_author\";s:1:\"8\";s:9:\"post_date\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 18:18:24\";s:13:\"post_date_gmt\";s:19:\"2012-05-08 18:18:24\";s:12:\"post_content\";s:4158:\"<h2>Locations</h2>\r\nThe 2015 Transitioning to College Writing Symposium will be held on the Oxford Campus of the University of Mississippi in the newly-renovated Jackson Avenue Center.\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"View a Map of Symposium Locations\" tag=\"h4\"]\r\n<a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Ole-Miss-Map.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-large wp-image-1343\" src=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Ole-Miss-Map-1024x675.jpg\" alt=\"Ole Miss Map\" width=\"598\" height=\"394\" /></a>\r\n\r\n[/expand]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Lodging</h2>\r\nWe have reserved a block of hotel rooms at the Inn at Ole Miss. To reserve your room, please call (662) 236-2500 and mention \"Transitioning to College Writing.\" You have until September 9, 2015 to reserve your room at the special rate of $109/night for standard accomodations.\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"Hotels and Motels\" tag=\"h4\"]\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.choicehotels.com/\">Comfort Inn</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-6000 • 1808 Jackson Avenue West\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://hamptoninn3.hilton.com/en/hotels/mississippi/hampton-inn-oxford-conference-center-OXDEAHX/index.html\">Hampton Inn East-Conference Center</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-5565 • 103 Ed Perry Blvd.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://hamptoninn3.hilton.com/en/hotels/mississippi/hampton-inn-oxford-west-OXDMSHX/accommodations/index.html\">Hampton Inn West</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-2442 • 110 Heritage Drive\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.theinnatolemiss.com/\">The Inn at Ole Miss</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-2331 • University of Mississippi\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.olemissmotel.com/\">Ole Miss Motel</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-2424 • 1517 University Avenue\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.super8.com/Super8/control/home\">Super 8</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-7013 • 2201 Jackson Avenue West\r\n\r\n<strong>University Inn</strong>\r\n(662) 234-9500 • 1101 Frontage Road\r\nPlease call hotel directly for reservations.\r\n\r\n[/expand]\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"Bed and Breakfast Inns\" tag=\"h4\"]\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://the512oxford.com/\">The 512 Bed and Breakfast </a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-8043 • 512 Van Buren Avenue\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thefarmatwillowdale.com/\"><strong>The Barn Loft at Willowdale Farm</strong></a>\r\n(662)801-8600 • 28 CR 225\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.bluecreekcabin.com/\">Blue Creek Cabin</a></strong>\r\n(662) 238-2897 • 535 Highway 30 East\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://burrowsbb.com/\">The Burrows</a></strong>\r\noff Highway 6 East • (662) 292-2220 • 40 CR 287\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.castlehilloxford.com/\">Castle Hill Resort </a></strong>\r\noff Highway 6 East • (662) 234-3735 • 120 Castlehill Drive\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.emptynestoxford.com/\"><strong>Empty Nest Guest House</strong></a></strong>\r\n(662) 801-9369 • 81 CR 231\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://littleqranch.com/index.html\"><strong>Little Q Ranch</strong></a></strong>\r\n(662) 801-5764 • 1018 CR 251\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://moonlightandmagnolias.weebly.com/\">Moonlight and Magnolias</a></strong>\r\n(662) 801-4768 •129 Cedar Hill Drive\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.oakhillstablesbedandbreakfast.com/\">Oak Hill Stables</a></strong>\r\n(662) 801-2084 • 670 County Road 101 (off Old Hwy.7)\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.oxfordravine.com/\">Ravine</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-4555 • 53 CR 321\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thez-oxford.com/page8.php\"><strong>The Z Bed and Breakfast</strong></a>\r\n(713)927-1295 • 1405 Pierce Ave\r\n\r\n[/expand]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Parking</h2>\r\nIf you indicate on the registration page that you will be bringing a car. No passes will be needed for the Thursday reception, because it is after 5:00pm. You can pick up your parking pass for Friday either at the reception banquet or on Friday morning at the Jackson Avenue Center. There is a large parking lot directly in front of our space at the Jackson Avenue Center.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Visitor-Parking-Map.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1066 size-medium\" src=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Visitor-Parking-Map-300x194.jpg\" alt=\"Visitor Parking Areas\" width=\"300\" height=\"194\" /></a>\";s:10:\"post_title\";s:18:\"Lodging and Travel\";s:12:\"post_excerpt\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_status\";s:7:\"publish\";s:14:\"comment_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:13:\"post_password\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"post_name\";s:6:\"travel\";s:7:\"to_ping\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"pinged\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"post_modified\";s:19:\"2015-09-04 19:42:56\";s:17:\"post_modified_gmt\";s:19:\"2015-09-04 19:42:56\";s:21:\"post_content_filtered\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"post_parent\";i:0;s:4:\"guid\";s:44:\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/?page_id=16\";s:10:\"menu_order\";i:0;s:9:\"post_type\";s