(1326, 27, '2014-10-01 12:23:03', '2014-10-01 12:23:03', '<h3 align=\"center\">About our Travel Grants</h3>\nThrough the generous contributions of various departments here at The University of Mississippi and the support of Bedford/St. Martin\'s, travel grants are available for a limited number of symposium attendees.\n\nWhile anyone registered for the symposium may apply for a grant, we have a limited amount of funds available, so applying for a grant does not guarantee a travel grant award. Thus, we prioritize by a combination of factors that include but are not limited to distance traveled, teacher access to professional development funds, school district policy regarding substitute pay, whether applicant is a new or returning symposium attendee, and date of application.\n\nDeadline to apply for a travel grant is Saturday, October 11, 2014. Recipients of travel grants will receive a check from us via postal service between October 15 and November 1.\n\nQuestions regarding travel grants should be sent to <a title=\"email link\" href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\" target=\"_blank\">transitioning@olemiss.edu</a>; phone call inquiries should be directed to 662-915-2121.\n\n<hr />\n\n[contact-form-7 id=\"107\" title=\"Grant Application\"]', 'Grants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '85-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-10-01 12:23:03', '2014-10-01 12:23:03', '', 85, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/85-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
