(1392, 1, '2014-11-20 20:11:31', '2014-11-20 20:11:31', '<h2>Locations</h2>\r\nThe 2014 Transitioning to College Writing Symposium will be held on the Oxford Campus of the University of Mississippi. Symposium events will be held in two locations: Friday morning events will be held in the Haley Barbour Center for Manufacturing Excellence, while Friday afternoon and Saturday events will be held in Lamar Hall, home of the Department of Writing and Rhetoric and the UM Oxford Writing Center. \r\n\r\n[expand title=\"View a Map of Symposium Locations\" tag=\"h4\"]\r\n<a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Ole-Miss-Map.jpg\"><img src=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Ole-Miss-Map-1024x675.jpg\" alt=\"Ole Miss Map\" width=\"598\" height=\"394\" class=\"alignleft size-large wp-image-1343\" /></a>\r\n<br/>\r\n[/expand]\r\n<hr/>\r\n<h2>Lodging</h2>\r\nWe have reserved a block of hotel rooms at the Holiday Inn Express on Heritage Drive, very close to campus. To reserve your room, please call (662) 236-2500 and mention \"College Writing Symposium.\" You have until September 10, 2014 to reserve your room at the special rate of $139/night. We have rooms with two queen size beds or 1 king and a pullout sleeper sofa. All guest rooms include a microwave, mini-fridge, iron and ironing board, coffee maker, cable with HBO, ceiling fans and complimentary wireless internet access.\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"Hotels and Motels\" tag=\"h4\"]\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.choicehotels.com/\">Comfort Inn</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-6000 • 1808 Jackson Avenue West\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://hamptoninn3.hilton.com/en/hotels/mississippi/hampton-inn-oxford-conference-center-OXDEAHX/index.html\">Hampton Inn East-Conference Center</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-5565 • 103 Ed Perry Blvd.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://hamptoninn3.hilton.com/en/hotels/mississippi/hampton-inn-oxford-west-OXDMSHX/accommodations/index.html\">Hampton Inn West</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-2442 • 110 Heritage Drive\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.theinnatolemiss.com/\">The Inn at Ole Miss</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-2331 • University of Mississippi\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.olemissmotel.com/\">Ole Miss Motel</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-2424 • 1517 University Avenue\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.super8.com/Super8/control/home\">Super 8</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-7013 • 2201 Jackson Avenue West\r\n\r\n<strong>University Inn</strong>\r\n(662) 234-9500 • 1101 Frontage Road\r\nPlease call hotel directly for reservations.\r\n\r\n[/expand]\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"Bed and Breakfast Inns\" tag=\"h4\"]\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://the512oxford.com/\">The 512 Bed and Breakfast </a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-8043 • 512 Van Buren Avenue\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thefarmatwillowdale.com/\"><strong>The Barn Loft at Willowdale Farm</strong></a>\r\n(662)801-8600 • 28 CR 225\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.bluecreekcabin.com/\">Blue Creek Cabin</a></strong>\r\n(662) 238-2897 • 535 Highway 30 East\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://burrowsbb.com/\">The Burrows</a></strong>\r\noff Highway 6 East • (662) 292-2220 • 40 CR 287\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.castlehilloxford.com/\">Castle Hill Resort </a></strong>\r\noff Highway 6 East • (662) 234-3735 • 120 Castlehill Drive\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.emptynestoxford.com/\"><strong>Empty Nest Guest House</strong></a></strong>\r\n(662) 801-9369 • 81 CR 231\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://littleqranch.com/index.html\"><strong>Little Q Ranch</strong></a></strong>\r\n(662) 801-5764 • 1018 CR 251\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://moonlightandmagnolias.weebly.com/\">Moonlight and Magnolias</a></strong>\r\n(662) 801-4768 •129 Cedar Hill Drive\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.oakhillstablesbedandbreakfast.com/\">Oak Hill Stables</a></strong>\r\n(662) 801-2084 • 670 County Road 101 (off Old Hwy.7)\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.oxfordravine.com/\">Ravine</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-4555 • 53 CR 321\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://thez-oxford.com/page8.php\"><strong>The Z Bed and Breakfast</strong></a>\r\n(713)927-1295 • 1405 Pierce Ave\r\n\r\n[/expand]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Parking</h2>\r\nIf you indicate on the registration page that you will be bringing a car, a parking pass will be mailed to you before the conference. The closest visitor parking to our events will be on the Circle by the Grove. Click the map below to view all the visitor parking areas.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Visitor-Parking-Map.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1066 size-medium\" src=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Visitor-Parking-Map-300x194.jpg\" alt=\"Visitor Parking Areas\" width=\"300\" height=\"194\" /></a>', 'Lodging and Travel', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-20 20:11:31', '2014-11-20 20:11:31', '', 16, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1391, 1, '2014-11-20 20:11:06', '2014-11-20 20:11:06', '<h2>Locations</h2>\r\nThe 2014 Transitioning to College Writing Symposium will be held on the Oxford Campus of the University of Mississippi. Symposium events will be held in two locations: Friday morning events will be held in the Haley Barbour Center for Manufacturing Excellence, while Friday afternoon and Saturday events will be held in Lamar Hall, home of the Department of Writing and Rhetoric and the UM Oxford Writing Center. \r\n\r\n[iframe src=\"http://map.olemiss.edu/?id=562&em=1&mrkIid=11257293\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" frameBorder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" border=\"0\" style=\"border:0px solid #fff; margin:0; padding:0;\"]\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"View a Map of Symposium Locations\" tag=\"h4\"]\r\n<a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Ole-Miss-Map.jpg\"><img src=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Ole-Miss-Map-1024x675.jpg\" alt=\"Ole Miss Map\" width=\"598\" height=\"394\" class=\"alignleft size-large wp-image-1343\" /></a>\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n[/expand]\r\n<hr/>\r\n<h2>Lodging</h2>\r\nWe have reserved a block of hotel rooms at the Holiday Inn Express on Heritage Drive, very close to campus. To reserve your room, please call (662) 236-2500 and mention \"College Writing Symposium.\" You have until September 10, 2014 to reserve your room at the special rate of $139/night. We have rooms with two queen size beds or 1 king and a pullout sleeper sofa. All guest rooms include a microwave, mini-fridge, iron and ironing board, coffee maker, cable with HBO, ceiling fans and complimentary wireless internet access.\r\n\r\n[expand title=\"Hotels and Motels\" tag=\"h4\"]\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://www.choicehotels.com/\">Comfort Inn</a></strong>\r\n(662) 234-6000 • 1808 Jackson Avenue West\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://hamptoninn3.hilton.com/en/hotels/mississippi/hampton-inn-oxford-conference-center-OXDEAHX/index.html\">Hampton Inn East-Conference Center