(1147, 1, '2014-09-16 15:44:06', '2014-09-16 15:44:06', '[responsive_vid]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nWe hope you will participate in this documentary project! We are excited to hear what you have to say about teaching writing in Mississippi and the Memphis area.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Please read and sign the release form before recording your responses.</li>\r\n	<li>Please identify yourself first, including your name and the name of the institution where you teach.</li>\r\n	<li>You may choose which questions to answer in your video response – do not feel obligated to answer them all, but focus on a few which you find particularly compelling, thought-provoking, or worth discussing.</li>\r\n	<li>We particularly would like variety in respondents - we’d love to have good representation from high schools, community colleges and four-year universities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<strong>Questions</strong>\r\n\r\n1. Why do you teach writing?\r\n2. What do you think is the most challenging thing about teaching writing at your institution?\r\n3. What challenges/opportunities does the context of our teaching – in Mississippi and the Memphis area – present?\r\n4. What do you wish students knew before they set foot in your class for the first time?\r\n5. What advice would you give a new teacher who is about to begin their first semester of teaching writing at your institution?\r\n6. What do you wish teachers at other institutions (i.e., community colleges and four-year universities, if you are a high school teacher; high schools and four-year universities, if you are a community college teacher, etc.) knew about how you teach your students?\r\n', 'Documentary Project', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '978-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-16 15:44:06', '2014-09-16 15:44:06', '', 978, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/978-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1136, 1, '2014-09-15 17:44:27', '2014-09-15 17:44:27', '[responsive_vid]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nThe Mississippi Teachers Talk documentary project continues this year! We will have a place set up on both Friday and Saturday for teachers to talk about their teaching and their students. Teachers may engage with one or more of the following questions:\r\n\r\n<strong>Questions</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How do you keep your writing instruction fresh from year to year?</li>\r\n	<li>How can we bring writing back to the forefront of the K-12 and college curriculum?</li>\r\n	<li>Are we, writing teachers, making a difference in our students\' lives?</li>\r\n	<li>Whose job is it to catch students who are struggling with writing and to struggle with them until they are able to succeed?</li>\r\n	<li>How do you foster student engagement with the revision process?</li>\r\n	<li>What has been your most successful strategy for peer review?</li>\r\n	<li>What strategies would you use to scaffold writing assignments for ESL students?</li>\r\n	<li>How has your approach to teaching writing evolved since your first experience?</li>\r\n	<li>What strategies do you use to help students revise and edit successfully?</li>\r\n	<li>How do you anticipate the expectations of each student\'s next academic level when making decisions about your curriculum?</li>\r\n	<li>How much do we do to promote Mississippi writers in our classrooms?</li>\r\n	<li>What, in your opinion, is the single most effective way to improve a student\'s writing?</li>\r\n	<li>How do you transition from the planning to the actual writing?</li>\r\n	<li>What is the very best writing assignment you ever gave your students, and what made it so effective?</li>\r\n	<li>In or outside of the classroom, what is the most challenging aspect of teaching writing for you?</li>\r\n	<li>Increasingly our students are predominantly kinesthetic learners. What are some practical strategies college writing teachers can use to keep these students engaged?</li>\r\n	<li>How do you explain to your students the difference between high school and college writing?</li>\r\n	<li>How do you teach your students the power of revision?</li>\r\n	<li>How do you get teachers in other disciplines to help students know the writing services your institution makes available?</li>\r\n	<li>What struggles or challenges do you see from high school seniors and Composition I students? How do you help them improve their writing?</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Documentary Project', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '978-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-15 17:44:27', '2014-09-15 17:44:27', '', 978, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/978-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
