(1293, 27, '2014-09-23 22:07:52', '2014-09-23 22:07:52', 'Please complete the form below to register for the Transitioning to College Writing Symposium. When you have submitted your registration information, you will receive a confirmation email. Please print this email for your records. <strong>Note</strong>: <strong>Online Registration Deadline: Friday, October 3, 2014</strong>. After that date, registrations will be accepted via phone (662.915.2121) or email (transitioning@olemiss.edu), or in-person at the Registration desk.\n\n<strong>Registration Fee: </strong>\n\n<strong>Friday Only - $30</strong>\n\n<strong>Saturday Only - $30</strong>\n\n<strong>Friday and Saturday - $50</strong>\n\nPlease send your payment by check to:\n\nDept. of Writing and Rhetoric\nAttn: Joanne Mitchell\nP.O. Box 1848\nLamar Hall, 3rd Floor, Suite B\nUniversity, MS 38655\n\n<strong>Q: May I pay with a PO (Purchase Order)? A: Yes.</strong> Here\'s how: Register as if you were sending in a check. Then, send an email to <a title=\"email registration information\" href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\" target=\"_blank\">transitioning@olemiss.edu</a> with your purchase order information and contact information. We will issue an invoice to the address you provide, referencing the purchase order; once we receive payment, a receipt will be sent to the address/contact you provide.\n\nTo pay with credit, debit, or PayPal, please follow the link at the bottom of this page after you submit the registration form.\n\nAfter registering, you will be added to the Transitioning listserv so that we can send you alerts and announcements via email. If you do not want to be added to the listserv, send an email to <a href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\">transitioning@olemiss.edu.</a>\n\nIf you have any questions about this form, please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\">transitioning@olemiss.edu</a> or (662) 915-2121.\n\n[contact-form-7 id=\"80\" title=\"Registration Form\"]\n\n<hr />\n\n<h3>About PayPal Registration</h3>\nIf you would like to pay for your Transitioning to College Writing Symposium registration using a credit or debit card, please enter your name below and select a registration type <strong>after</strong> submitting your registration above. Since we process credit and debit cards using PayPal, we need you to enter your name and registration type a second time so we can confirm your payment.\n\n[wp_paypal_payment]\n\n<hr />', 'Registration', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-09-23 22:07:52', '2014-09-23 22:07:52', '', 77, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/77-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1237, 1, '2014-09-23 16:27:38', '2014-09-23 16:27:38', 'We invite you to join us on September 28 and 29 of this year, as writing teachers from college and high school settings in Mississippi and the Memphis areas meet here on the Ole Miss campus to explore challenges we all face in giving our students the best possible foundation for transitioning to college writing.\r\n\r\nOur program begins Friday morning with a welcoming address and moves into various workshops, keynote addresses, round tables, and “unconference” forums that we hope will foster dialogue, encourage the communication of values and teaching practices, and promote understanding between all of us.\r\n\r\nDuring our two days together, we will engage with the following questions:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>What are the experiences of students in Mississippi as they write during their high school and college years?</li>\r\n	<li>How is writing taught across these settings?</li>\r\n	<li>How is standardized testing, such as the English II Writing Assessment, ACT, and the SAT, affecting writing curricula in secondary schools?</li>\r\n	<li>What is expected of college writers?</li>\r\n	<li>How are teachers helping students develop as lifelong writers, such as creative writers, citizen writers and workplace writers?</li>\r\n	<li>What resources are teachers of writing using to facilitate their work?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlso, attendees will have the opportunity to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Meet and network with other teachers of writing from high school and college venues</li>\r\n	<li>Great resources to use and share: handbooks, textbooks, assignment swaps, and more</li>\r\n	<li>Map the landscape of writing in our area, using guided activities and workshop sessions</li>\r\n</ul>', '2012 Transitioning to College Writing Symposium', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1151-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-23 16:27:38', '2014-09-23 16:27:38', '', 1151, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/1151-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
