(1238, 1, '2014-09-23 16:28:07', '2014-09-23 16:28:07', '&nbsp;\r\n<table id=\"table-3\" border=\"5\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"td-1\" style=\"text-align: center;\" colspan=\"5\"><strong>Friday, September 28, 2012</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>7:30-8:30</strong></td>\r\n<td class=\"td-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" colspan=\"4\"><em>Union Ballroom</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\">\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Buffet Style Breakfast</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>8:30-9:00</strong></td>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Welcome</strong>\r\nDr. Robert E. Cummings, Director of the Center for Writing and Rhetoric</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Opening Remarks</strong>\r\nDr. Andy Mullins, Chief of Staff to the Chancellor, and Associate Professor of Leadership &amp; Counselor Education and Co-Director of Mississippi Teacher Corps</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>9:00-9:15</strong></td>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Video Vignettes</strong> of writing teachers, writing students, writing tutors and directors- presenting schools, teachers, and student from high schools, 2- and 4-year colleges, and writing centers</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>9:15-10:00</strong></td>\r\n<td class=\"td-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\" width=\"40%\"><em>405 A &amp; B</em></td>\r\n<td class=\"td-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\" width=\"40%\"><em>404 A &amp; B</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Plenary Session IA</strong>\r\n“Standards to Teach By: The Common Core &amp; the Framework for Success in Postsecondary Writing Standards and How They Affect Teaching Writing at All Levels”- Dr. Ellen Shelton with Tara Gilstrap (University of Mississippi) and Mary Ann Parker (DeSoto Central High School)</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Plenary Session IB</strong>\r\n“Building Bridges for Transition: Supporting Writing Classrooms with Writing Centers” (A Resource Tool Kit)- Amber Jensen, Writing Center Sponsor (Edison High School) and Anna Britt-Begnaud, Writing Center Director (Itawamba Community College). Includes question and answer session.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>10:00-10:15</strong></td>\r\n<td class=\"td-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" colspan=\"4\"><em>Union Ballroom</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\">\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Introduction of Cluster Meeting Strategies- a how to session with handouts and Morning Break</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>10:15-11:00</strong></td>\r\n<td class=\"td-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" colspan=\"4\"><em>403, 404A, 404B, 405A, 405B, Catalpha, 412</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Cluster Session I:</strong> In small groups, attendees will explore and discuss current topics, and then select one for which the group will develop (in session 2) interventions, strategies, and resources for sharing with Saturday’s attendees.  Guidelines will be distributed.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\"><strong>11:00-11:55</strong></td>\r\n<td class=\"td-2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" colspan=\"4\"><em>Union Ballroom</em></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Plenary Session IIA</strong>Part 1 (11:00 - 11:25)\r\n\"It’s All About Location: Reflections on Student Preparedness and the Transfer of Knowledge\"\r\nDr. Chris Anson</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\"><strong>Plenary Session IIB</strong>Part 2 (11:25 - 11:55)\r\nTeaching Writing in the 21st Century: Question and Answer Open Session with Dr. Chris Anson</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td