(1325, 27, '2014-09-30 21:12:57', '2014-09-30 21:12:57', 'Please complete the form below to register for the Transitioning to College Writing Symposium. When you have submitted your registration information, you will receive a confirmation email. Please print this email for your records. <strong>Note</strong>: <strong>Online Registration Deadline: Monday, October 6, 2014</strong>. After that date, registrations will be taken via phone (662.915.2121) or email (<a title=\"email for transitioning registration\" href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\" target=\"_blank\">transitioning@olemiss.edu</a>), or in-person at the Registration desk on October 10.\r\n\r\n<strong>Registration Fee: </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Friday Only - $30</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday Only - $30</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Friday and Saturday - $50</strong>\r\n\r\nPlease send your payment by check to:\r\n\r\nDept. of Writing and Rhetoric\r\nAttn: Joanne Mitchell\r\nP.O. Box 1848\r\nLamar Hall, 3rd Floor, Suite B\r\nUniversity, MS 38655\r\n\r\n<strong>Q: May I pay with a PO (Purchase Order)? A: Yes.</strong> Here\'s how: Register as if you were sending in a check. Then, send an email to <a title=\"email registration information\" href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\" target=\"_blank\">transitioning@olemiss.edu</a> with your purchase order information and contact information. We will issue an invoice to the address you provide, referencing the purchase order; once we receive payment, a receipt will be sent to the address/contact you provide.\r\n\r\nTo pay with credit, debit, or PayPal, please follow the link at the bottom of this page after you submit the registration form.\r\n\r\nAfter registering, you will be added to the Transitioning listserv so that we can send you alerts and announcements via email. If you do not want to be added to the listserv, send an email to <a href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\">transitioning@olemiss.edu.</a>\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions about this form, please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\">transitioning@olemiss.edu</a> or (662) 915-2121.\r\n\r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"80\" title=\"Registration Form\"]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>About PayPal Registration</h3>\r\nIf you would like to pay for your Transitioning to College Writing Symposium registration using a credit or debit card, please enter your name below and select a registration type <strong>after</strong> submitting your registration above. Since we process credit and debit cards using PayPal, we need you to enter your name and registration type a second time so we can confirm your payment.\r\n\r\n[wp_paypal_payment]\r\n\r\n<hr />', 'Registration', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-30 21:12:57', '2014-09-30 21:12:57', '', 77, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/77-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1327, 27, '2014-10-01 12:21:42', '2014-10-01 12:21:42', '<h3 align=\"center\">About our Travel Grants</h3>\r\nThrough the generous contributions of various departments here at The University of Mississippi and the support of Bedford/St. Martin\'s/Macmillan Publishing, travel grants are available for a limited number of symposium attendees.\r\n\r\nWhile anyone registered for the symposium may apply for a grant, we have a limited amount of funds available, so applying for a grant does not guarantee a travel grant award. Thus, we prioritize by a combination of factors that include but are not limited to distance traveled, teacher access to professional development funds, school district policy regarding substitute pay, whether applicant is a new or returning symposium attendee, and date of application.\r\n\r\nDeadline to apply for a travel grant is Saturday, October 11, 2014. Recipients of travel grants will receive a check from us via postal service between October 15 and November 1.\r\n\r\nQuestions regarding travel grants should be sent to transitioning@olemiss.edu; phone call inquiries should be directed to 662-915-2121.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"107\" title=\"Grant Application\"]', 'Grants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '85-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-01 12:21:42', '2014-10-01 12:21:42', '', 85, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/85-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
