(1460, 3, '2015-06-12 21:07:41', '2015-06-12 21:07:41', 'Each year, the Department of Writing and Rhetoric, along with other UM partners, hosts a themed Transitioning to College Writing Symposium in support of writing instruction in our area.\r\n\r\nThis year\'s theme is \"Listen, Think, Respond: Engaging Students in Writing for Life.\" Continuing in our tradition of creating and welcoming cross-institutional conversations about teaching writing, we welcome teachers from secondary and post-secondary classrooms. We invite you to join us on October 1 and 2 as we share ideas, meet new and old friends and colleagues, and talk about the rewards and challenges we have in common.\r\n\r\nWe are currently accepting proposals for the 2015 Transitioning to College Writing Symposium. Please visit our <a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/about/cfp/\">Call for Proposals page</a> to submit a workshop, poster, or individual session for this year\'s symposium.', 'About the 2015 Symposium', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-12 21:07:41', '2015-06-12 21:07:41', '', 6, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1461, 3, '2015-06-12 21:08:36', '2015-06-12 21:08:36', 'Each year, the Department of Writing and Rhetoric, along with other <a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/sponsors/\">UM partners</a>, hosts a themed Transitioning to College Writing Symposium in support of writing instruction in our area.\r\n\r\nThis year\'s theme is \"Listen, Think, Respond: Engaging Students in Writing for Life.\" Continuing in our tradition of creating and welcoming cross-institutional conversations about teaching writing, we welcome teachers from secondary and post-secondary classrooms. We invite you to join us on October 1 and 2 as we share ideas, meet new and old friends and colleagues, and talk about the rewards and challenges we have in common.\r\n\r\nWe are currently accepting proposals for the 2015 Transitioning to College Writing Symposium. Please visit our <a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/about/cfp/\">Call for Proposals page</a> to submit a workshop, poster, or individual session for this year\'s symposium.', 'About the 2015 Symposium', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-12 21:08:36', '2015-06-12 21:08:36', '', 6, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1476, 3, '2015-07-01 14:49:16', '2015-07-01 14:49:16', '<h3 align=\"center\">About our Travel Grants</h3>\nThrough the generous contributions from the College of Liberal Arts and the School of Education, travel grants are available for a limited number of symposium attendees.\n\nWhile anyone registered for the symposium may apply for a grant, we have a limited amount of funds available, so applying for a grant does not guarantee a travel grant award. Thus, we prioritize by a combination of factors that include but are not limited to distance traveled, teacher access to professional development funds, school district policy regarding substitute pay, whether the applicant is a new or returning symposium attendee, and the date of application.\n\nDeadline to apply for a travel grant is Friday, October 2, 2015. Recipients of travel grants will receive a check from us via postal service between November 1 and November 30.\n\nQuestions regarding travel grants should be sent to <a title=\"email link\" href=\"mailto:transitioning@olemiss.edu\" target=\"_blank\">transitioning@olemiss.edu</a>; phone call inquiries should be directed to 662-915-2121.\n\n<hr />\n\n[contact-form-7 id=\"107\" title=\"Grant Application\"]', 'Grants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '85-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-07-01 14:49:16', '2015-07-01 14:49:16', '', 85, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/85-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1464, 3, '2015-06-12 21:11:34', '2015-06-12 21:11:34', 'Welcome to the Transitioning to College Writing Symposium website, hosted by the Department of Writing and Rhetoric at the University of Mississippi.\r\n\r\n<strong>The <a href=\"http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/about/cfp/\">Call for Participation</a> for this year\'s symposium is now available! We encourage everyone to submit. Please have proposals in by July 15, 2015.</strong>\r\n\r\nTransitioning to College Writing is an annual symposium for writing teachers from college and high school settings in Mississippi and the Memphis areas. Held on the Ole Miss campus, attendees explore challenges we all face in giving our students the best possible foundation for transitioning to college writing.\r\n<h3>Welcome and Preview of the 2015 Transitioning to College Writing Symposium</h3>\r\n[responsive_vid]', 'Welcome!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1103-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-12 21:11:34', '2015-06-12 21:11:34', '', 1103, 'http://transitioning.olemiss.edu/1103-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
